  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      In 5 Belgian hospitals, the data of 100 CLI-patients receiving the cryoplasty technique to
      treat their infrapopliteal arterial lesions will be collected. The treatment occurs strictly
      according the &quot;Instructions For Use&quot; of the CE-approved device (PolarCath Peripheral
      Dilatation System, Boston Scientific) and only data are collected that have been made
      available conform the Standard the Standards of Care for these patients.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
